Discussion written to `discussion.md`. Summary: criterion 1 (λ_1 > 0) passes, criterion 2 (~40% spectrum match) fails due to the near-zero λ_2 being over-contracted by 10×, and criterion 3 (vs p10 baseline) cannot be assessed from this directory alone. The LC sweep landscape is monotonic — no loop-closure weight improves on lc=0 for trajectory prediction. Overall hypothesis is mixed: p=30 recovers the dominant and most-contracted exponents well but does not resolve the near-neutral direction.
